ans/2026-03-10-attach-checkpoint-id.md\",\"content\":\"# Attach Command: Return Checkpoint ID\\n\\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (if subagents available) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\\n\\n**Goal:** Make `entire attach` condense the session immediately and print `Entire-Checkpoint: <id>` so the user can paste it into a commit message.\\n\\n**Architecture:** After `SaveStep` succeeds, generate a checkpoint ID via `id.Generate()`, open the repo, call `CondenseSession()` to persist metadata to `entire/checkpoints/v1`, update session state (mirroring `CondenseSessionByID`), and print the trailer line.\\n\\n**Tech Stack:** Go, go-git, existing strategy/checkpoint/id packages\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Task 1: Add condensation + checkpoint ID output to attach command\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/attach.go:48-211` (runAttach function)\\n- Test: `cmd/entire/cli/attach_test.go`\\n\\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write failing test for checkpoint ID in output**\\n\\nAdd a test that verifies `runAttach` output contains `Entire-Checkpoint:` followed by a 12-hex-char ID.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc TestAttach_OutputContainsCheckpointID(t *testing.T) {\\n\\ttmpDir := t.TempDir()\\n\\ttestutil.InitRepo(t, tmpDir)\\n\\ttestutil.WriteFile(t, tmpDir, \\\"init.txt\\\", \\\"init\\\")\\n\\ttestutil.GitAdd(t, tmpDir, \\\"init.txt\\\")\\n\\ttestutil.GitCommit(t, tmpDir, \\\"init\\\")\\n\\tt.Chdir(tmpDir)\\n\\n\\tenableEntire(t, tmpDir)\\n\\n\\tclaudeDir := t.TempDir()\\n\\tt.Setenv(\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR\\\", claudeDir)\\n\\n\\tsessionID := \\\"test-attach-checkpoint-output\\\"\\n\\ttranscriptContent := `{\\\"type\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"hello\\\"},\\\"uuid\\\":\\\"uuid-1\\\"}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"tool_use\\\",\\\"id\\\":